  "why": "The paper goes beyond simply reporting failures: it analyzes statistical patterns (counts of failures per ASR and per TTS), uses these patterns to compare ASR reliability, and performs a manual diagnostic analysis of false positives that attributes many failures to external causes (TTS quality, text-normalization/preprocessing issues, or ambiguous audio). However, it does not trace failures to underlying ASR model vulnerabilities (e.g., biased or corrupted training data, spurious features, overfitting) nor inspects model internals (neuron activations, coverage, etc.). Thus the paper provides partial diagnostic insight but not root-cause explanations tied to the ASR models themselves.",
